WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:08.416
♪ La-la-la-la, la-la-la-la ♪

00:08.500 --> 00:09.916
-[grunts]
-Mmm.

00:11.000 --> 00:14.333
[Wammawink] ♪ La-la-la-la, la-la-la-la ♪

00:14.416 --> 00:15.833
♪ La-la-la ♪

00:17.625 --> 00:19.708
[Centaurs laughing, humming]

00:19.791 --> 00:21.541
-[Horse screaming]
-[gasps]

00:21.625 --> 00:23.583
[Horse laughing]

00:23.666 --> 00:25.083
[Centaurs yelling excitedly]

00:26.208 --> 00:28.458
-[Zulius groans, cries]
-[gasps] Oh.

00:28.541 --> 00:30.250
[groaning]

00:30.333 --> 00:32.916
♪ One careful step at a time ♪

00:33.833 --> 00:36.041
♪ Please watch yourselves as you go ♪

00:37.708 --> 00:39.375
♪ Better safe than sorry ♪

00:39.458 --> 00:43.041
♪ Never made it this far
We ought to take it slow ♪

00:44.083 --> 00:45.166
[snorts]

00:45.250 --> 00:50.500
♪ For we are all just fragile things
Soft and small ♪

00:50.583 --> 00:53.500
♪ And haven't been here before ♪

00:53.583 --> 00:56.583
♪ Where the outside can harm you
Reject you ♪

00:56.666 --> 01:00.291
♪ But just stay close
And I will protect you ♪

01:00.375 --> 01:01.916
[loud thud]

01:02.000 --> 01:03.833
[music builds]

01:08.333 --> 01:12.541
♪ Oh, I never feared the drums of war ♪

01:12.625 --> 01:16.208
♪ I crushed the skulls and I want more ♪

01:16.291 --> 01:19.458
♪ While you're hiding in the fringes ♪

01:20.083 --> 01:23.250
♪ I'll go out and I'll get my vengeance ♪

01:23.333 --> 01:30.000
-♪ You can all be fearless, too ♪
-[Centaurs] ♪ Fearless, too ♪

01:30.083 --> 01:33.750
♪ You can fight for yourselves
You're all right by yourselves ♪

01:33.833 --> 01:37.041
♪ 'Cause you know
Only you can protect you ♪

01:37.125 --> 01:37.958
No!

01:38.041 --> 01:41.041
♪ We are all just fragile things
Soft and small ♪

01:41.125 --> 01:43.041
♪ You can all be fearless, too ♪

01:43.125 --> 01:45.958
-♪ Haven't been here before ♪
-♪ You can fight for yourselves ♪

01:46.041 --> 01:48.625
-♪ Outside can harm you ♪
-♪ All right by yourselves ♪

01:48.708 --> 01:50.541
-♪ 'Cause you know ♪
-♪ Just stay close ♪

01:50.625 --> 01:53.041
-♪ Only you can protect you ♪
-♪ I'll protect you ♪

01:53.125 --> 01:54.958
[both] ♪ You! You! You! You! ♪

01:55.041 --> 02:00.875
♪ See, this is why
I should be leading the way ♪

02:01.708 --> 02:04.083
-♪ Because I'll keep you safe ♪
-♪ Make you strong ♪

02:04.166 --> 02:10.500
[both] ♪ Stop it! Clearly, she's wrong
You should believe me when I say ♪

02:11.541 --> 02:13.666
[all grunt, hit the ground]

02:17.000 --> 02:18.750
[birds calling]

02:21.291 --> 02:26.208
-♪ For we are all just fragile things ♪
-♪ You can all… ♪

02:26.291 --> 02:28.166
-♪ Soft and small ♪
-♪ …be fearless too ♪

02:28.250 --> 02:31.416
-♪ Haven't been here before ♪
-♪ You can fight for yourselves ♪

02:31.500 --> 02:34.708
-♪ Where the outside can harm you ♪
-♪ You're all right by yourselves ♪

02:34.791 --> 02:38.666
[both] ♪ But just stay close to me ♪

02:40.083 --> 02:44.791
♪ Oh, I never feared the drums of war ♪

02:44.875 --> 02:51.458
♪ I crushed the skulls and I want more ♪

02:54.250 --> 02:57.958
[Wammawink] ♪ In Centaurworld ♪

02:58.041 --> 03:00.666
-[neighing]
-[vocalizing]

03:00.750 --> 03:01.833
[squeaks]

03:03.666 --> 03:05.208
Mm-hmm. [grunts]

03:05.291 --> 03:08.541
[chuckles embarrassingly]
I don't think anyone noticed.

03:09.250 --> 03:12.791
-Whew! Okay, then.
-That's what I was just talking about.

03:12.875 --> 03:15.666
You have to be careful.
Don't step in anyone's--

03:15.750 --> 03:17.250
[groans] Oh!

03:17.333 --> 03:19.708
[chuckles] Fun.

03:19.791 --> 03:21.500
Hmm… Dumpies ditch.

03:21.583 --> 03:23.166
-[groans]
-[grunts]

03:23.250 --> 03:26.083
-Stay away from the Wasptaurs!
-[squeaks]

03:26.916 --> 03:27.916
[sighs]

03:28.000 --> 03:30.750
Did anyone even listen to my song?

03:30.833 --> 03:32.083
[Zulius] Your song?

03:32.166 --> 03:34.166
Technically, it was a duet.

03:34.250 --> 03:36.583
And her verse was much more compelling.

03:36.666 --> 03:38.708
More evocative imagery. [chuckles]

03:38.791 --> 03:42.416
Notes of… [sniffing] fig and, wait…

03:42.500 --> 03:44.875
-[sniffing] Yeah. Murder.
-Focus up.

03:44.958 --> 03:48.208
We aren't on some leisurely stroll.
We need to get to…

03:48.291 --> 03:49.416
[inhales deeply]

03:49.500 --> 03:51.875
[echoing] …the Shaman.

03:51.958 --> 03:53.750
[ethereal music plays]

03:53.833 --> 03:55.125
[duck quacks]

03:56.958 --> 03:58.083
Mmm, let's go.

03:58.166 --> 03:59.458
[whimpering]

04:00.833 --> 04:05.416
-[sighs] Something wrong, Glendale?
-Need to make splashy right now! [grunts]

04:05.500 --> 04:06.875
Uh, sorry?

04:06.958 --> 04:10.708
She needs to use
the tinkle tinkle bye-bye zone.

04:10.791 --> 04:12.000
[groans]

04:12.625 --> 04:15.833
-Everybody outta my way. I've gotta go!
-[sighs] Anyone else?

04:15.916 --> 04:19.541
I can't believe you're looking at me
and thinking that I use--

04:19.625 --> 04:21.166
There's a mirror in there.

04:21.708 --> 04:24.625
-I'll be right back.
-Oh, and they got mints, too!

04:24.708 --> 04:26.041
[ethereal music plays]

04:26.125 --> 04:27.208
[groans]

04:27.291 --> 04:31.333
Ha, who forgot to put merry berries
on her Cheerful-O's this morning?

04:31.416 --> 04:34.333
-I don't eat breakfast. I…
-[hand dryer whooshing]

04:35.708 --> 04:37.833
You should always eat breakfast.

04:37.916 --> 04:39.166
I don't need to eat.

04:39.250 --> 04:40.625
Okay? I'm on a mission.

04:40.708 --> 04:43.375
Hi, Mona Mission. Nice to meet you.

04:43.458 --> 04:44.791
[Centaurs laugh]

04:46.083 --> 04:47.666
-That's not my name.
-Ooh!

04:47.750 --> 04:49.000
Is it Lanabelle?

04:49.083 --> 04:50.583
-No.
-Splashy?

04:50.666 --> 04:52.125
As in pee? No!

04:52.208 --> 04:54.333
Bamanda? Jonathan Tendergreens?

04:54.416 --> 04:56.041
Bunter? Clemmums Time?

04:56.125 --> 04:59.458
Horse! I already told you.
You can call me Horse.

04:59.541 --> 05:01.375
Horse. Boring and forgettable.

05:01.458 --> 05:04.833
-It's perfect.
-Do you have some sort of problem with me?

05:04.916 --> 05:07.583
-Uh, actually, yeah.
-Let's just keep moving.

05:09.875 --> 05:11.375
[grunting]

05:11.458 --> 05:13.291
[sighs] Just go.

05:13.375 --> 05:14.375
[squeals]

05:17.833 --> 05:19.416
-[toilet flushing]
-[sighs]

05:20.041 --> 05:21.916
[Glendale humming]

05:22.000 --> 05:24.000
-[giggling]
-[continues humming]

05:29.041 --> 05:31.958
So, you're sure
this shaman thing can get me home?

05:32.041 --> 05:33.166
Of course!

05:33.250 --> 05:37.083
Shamans are the most magical creatures
in all of Centaurworld.

05:37.166 --> 05:39.500
I should know. Shamans and I go way back.

05:39.583 --> 05:41.625
She knows them from shaman school.

05:41.708 --> 05:44.041
Wammawink was their number one student.

05:44.125 --> 05:48.125
[scoffs] I don't know about number one,
but I was certainly up there.

05:48.208 --> 05:49.041
So, wait.

05:49.125 --> 05:52.750
I mean, if you went to shaman school,
why aren't you a shaman?

05:52.833 --> 05:54.791
[laughs nervously] What? Well, I…

05:54.875 --> 05:59.000
I mean, um, it was more
of a continuing education situation.

05:59.083 --> 06:00.583
[gasps] Wait.

06:00.666 --> 06:02.083
[ominous music playing]

06:04.250 --> 06:06.500
-We can't go this way.
-I don't get it. Why not?

06:06.583 --> 06:09.708
I'm getting a bad feeling
about this place.

06:09.791 --> 06:12.625
A sense that something
very dangerous lies ahead.

06:13.291 --> 06:14.833
Uh, we should turn back.

06:14.916 --> 06:17.375
Turn back? What are you talking about?

06:17.458 --> 06:19.875
I have the ability to predict the future.

06:20.583 --> 06:21.625
Sometimes.

06:22.500 --> 06:23.583
-Zulius.
-Gasp.

06:23.666 --> 06:26.875
Remember when I was certain you
were gonna get a pimple on your eyelid?

06:26.958 --> 06:28.708
-And you did?
-[quavers] Aah!

06:28.791 --> 06:32.416
And not just a regular pimple.
A really nasty one.

06:32.500 --> 06:34.666
[screams] No idea
what you're talking about.

06:34.750 --> 06:35.791
Oh, come on.

06:35.875 --> 06:38.375
It's true.
The scab fell off and I kept it.

06:38.458 --> 06:39.833
And I named him Bunter.

06:39.916 --> 06:44.000
I'm really glad that's not your name,
Horse. That would get confusing.

06:44.583 --> 06:46.916
Hey, can I have some money?

06:47.958 --> 06:51.250
Okay. You know what?
Thank you for everything. I just--

06:51.333 --> 06:55.750
I'm just gonna stay on the road.
I'm sure I can find the Shaman on my own.

06:55.833 --> 06:59.000
You're all welcome to stay here
hiding in your domes, naming scabs,

06:59.083 --> 07:01.000
and pretending you can predict the future.

07:01.083 --> 07:03.583
I'm not pretending! Hmm.

07:03.666 --> 07:06.375
-Ugh. Goodbye. Good--
-Wait.

07:06.875 --> 07:08.041
Hold on, guys.

07:08.125 --> 07:10.125
We can't let her go alone.

07:10.208 --> 07:14.291
We promised we'd get her to the Shaman.

07:14.375 --> 07:17.958
-And?
-And, as Bunter always says…

07:18.041 --> 07:21.583
[Durpleton and Glendale]
"A Centaur always keeps its promises."

07:21.666 --> 07:23.750
Bunter said that? [laughs]

07:23.833 --> 07:27.125
That doesn't sound like Bunter.
Not that I've ever had a pimple.

07:27.208 --> 07:29.333
I'm sorry, but it's not safe to go on.

07:29.416 --> 07:32.958
-We never should've left the valley.
-I wouldn't go that far.

07:33.041 --> 07:35.625
I don't wanna be cooped up
in that happy dome.

07:35.708 --> 07:39.916
I don't wanna go back to smelling
the same flowers we've always smelt.

07:40.000 --> 07:43.083
Or stealing the same flowers
we've always stole--

07:43.166 --> 07:45.875
Oh, I mean, borrowing. Just borrowing.

07:45.958 --> 07:49.208
And to be honest,
our tinkle tinkle bye-bye zone at home

07:49.291 --> 07:51.125
was more of a dumpies ditch.

07:51.208 --> 07:52.916
So what are you saying?

07:53.000 --> 07:55.708
-You wanna go with her?
-[all] Mmm…

07:55.791 --> 08:00.166
I don't know if you're jealous of Horse
or if you just don't believe in us,

08:00.250 --> 08:02.416
but we should keep our promise.

08:02.500 --> 08:03.833
[gentle music playing]

08:05.500 --> 08:06.625
Come on, Wammawink.

08:06.708 --> 08:10.375
I've still got lots of space
in this tummy that I need help fillin'.

08:11.583 --> 08:12.583
[inhales deeply]

08:12.666 --> 08:18.583
Ugh, I can't believe I'm going to do this,
but fine. Let's go.

08:22.875 --> 08:26.750
-Hey! Wait up!
-I thought you were turning back.

08:26.833 --> 08:29.500
Wammawink's bad feeling about this place
and all that.

08:29.583 --> 08:32.166
We wanted to feel the winds in our manes!

08:32.250 --> 08:34.000
[wind whooshes]

08:35.583 --> 08:37.958
[cackles] Oh! Oh, oh!

08:38.041 --> 08:41.375
-[thunder rumbling]
-Look at that! It's touching down!

08:41.458 --> 08:45.500
I bet it's gonna come right this way!
Reminds me of the chaos of home!

08:45.583 --> 08:47.333
[laughs triumphantly]

08:47.416 --> 08:49.291
-Whoo-hoo!
-See?

08:49.375 --> 08:52.333
I told ya! We have to take cover!

08:52.416 --> 08:54.500
Okay, Wammawink. Question for you.

08:55.083 --> 08:56.666
Which way is the Shaman?

08:57.250 --> 09:00.208
Well, technically, it's, um…

09:00.833 --> 09:01.833
It's that way.

09:01.916 --> 09:03.833
Correct. It's that way.

09:04.541 --> 09:06.458
I'm going that way.

09:06.541 --> 09:09.166
Besides, it's just a tornado.

09:09.791 --> 09:12.500
You know, wind on the go.

09:13.125 --> 09:14.750
[cackles]

09:16.291 --> 09:20.958
Uh, Horse, you forgot your foot stuff.

09:21.791 --> 09:23.291
[whimpers]

09:24.708 --> 09:26.000
[farts] Hoo! Hah!

09:26.083 --> 09:28.000
I'm sorry. I'm going, I'm going!

09:28.083 --> 09:30.083
[ominous music playing]

09:31.333 --> 09:33.875
Hey! What are you doing?

09:33.958 --> 09:36.625
Horse is wrong! This is not a tornado.

09:36.708 --> 09:38.291
[ominous music continues]

09:39.541 --> 09:40.791
[eerie neigh]

09:40.875 --> 09:43.458
It's a Taurnado!

09:44.625 --> 09:46.166
[thunder crashing]

09:46.250 --> 09:48.291
[Taurnado] ♪ Come to us ♪

09:48.375 --> 09:51.791
♪ I've never feared the drums of war ♪

09:51.875 --> 09:53.791
[Taurnado] ♪ You will be ours ♪

09:53.875 --> 09:57.666
♪ I've faced down
Far worse things before ♪

09:57.750 --> 10:02.708
-[Taurnado] ♪ In the skies ♪
-[Horse] ♪ But never has it counted more ♪

10:02.791 --> 10:07.000
-[Taurnado] ♪ Forever ♪
-[Horse] ♪ Than now ♪

10:07.750 --> 10:09.791
[Taurnado] ♪ Won't let you go ♪

10:09.875 --> 10:14.875
-♪ You're okay if you stick with me ♪
-[Taurnado] ♪ Don't leave our side ♪

10:14.958 --> 10:18.708
[Horse] ♪ 'Cause I can teach you
How to be ♪

10:18.791 --> 10:23.958
-[Taurnado] ♪ How will you hide? ♪
-♪ Quicker, stronger, full of bravery ♪

10:24.041 --> 10:27.500
♪ And how ♪

10:27.583 --> 10:31.375
♪ To survive ♪

10:31.458 --> 10:35.333
[Taurnado] ♪ You can't escape from us ♪

10:35.416 --> 10:36.625
The Artifact! No!

10:36.708 --> 10:40.166
[Taurnado] ♪ You were all made for us ♪

10:41.375 --> 10:42.750
♪ Just give up ♪

10:42.833 --> 10:44.208
Mmm, shiny boy!

10:44.291 --> 10:48.000
-Glendale, no!
-Don't worry. You're safe with me now.

10:48.541 --> 10:49.791
Whoa!

10:49.875 --> 10:51.458
[yelps] Whoa!

10:51.541 --> 10:52.541
[grunting]

10:52.625 --> 10:55.083
Bubblegum. Apple Bottom jeans.

10:55.166 --> 10:57.291
Can't fight it anymore, Horse!

10:58.916 --> 11:01.583
♪ Now I am yours ♪

11:01.666 --> 11:03.083
[Horse] Wait! No!

11:03.166 --> 11:04.875
♪ I'll live up in the skies ♪

11:04.958 --> 11:06.208
Hang on!

11:06.791 --> 11:10.791
[Glendale] ♪ Forevermore ♪

11:12.791 --> 11:19.416
[Taurnado] ♪ You are now
One of our thousands of souls ♪

11:19.500 --> 11:24.625
♪ We've taken and lifted above ♪

11:24.708 --> 11:26.000
[thunder rumbling]

11:26.083 --> 11:29.916
♪ You are ours ♪

11:30.541 --> 11:34.166
-♪ And we are yours ♪
-[Glendale screaming]

11:35.250 --> 11:39.416
[Taurnado] ♪ You can't escape from us ♪

11:41.083 --> 11:44.583
♪ You are all made for us ♪

11:46.000 --> 11:48.625
♪ Just give up
Just give in ♪

11:48.708 --> 11:52.125
♪ You are all ours now ♪

11:53.333 --> 11:55.416
♪ Just give in to us now ♪

11:55.500 --> 11:56.708
[Centaurs screaming]

12:00.291 --> 12:02.416
[Centaurs screaming]

12:02.500 --> 12:03.500
[groaning]

12:04.208 --> 12:06.083
Wow! [laughs]

12:06.166 --> 12:07.583
That was something, huh?

12:08.083 --> 12:10.500
Why'd you kick us into the Taurnado?

12:10.583 --> 12:14.916
Well, that is a fair question,
but I mean, it worked, right? You got out.

12:15.000 --> 12:16.083
-[mumbles]
-[gasps]

12:16.166 --> 12:18.708
Hey, Glendale, give me my dingus.

12:18.791 --> 12:20.500
[Glendale whimpers]

12:21.458 --> 12:23.875
-Cold.
-Cool. Glad we got that figured out.

12:23.958 --> 12:25.666
-Let's roll!
-[Wammawink] No!

12:26.208 --> 12:29.000
-Wha--
-Don't you even care how they're feeling?

12:29.083 --> 12:31.416
-They put themselves in danger for you.
-[groaning]

12:31.500 --> 12:34.291
Glendale threw herself into a Taurnado.

12:34.375 --> 12:35.666
Oh, hi.

12:35.750 --> 12:37.916
Me? [laughs]

12:38.000 --> 12:39.708
Let's call a spade a spade.

12:39.791 --> 12:42.291
She was just after this
because it's shiny.

12:42.375 --> 12:44.166
-[Glendale whimpering]
-Let me finish.

12:44.250 --> 12:47.375
You don't know her
and you don't care about her.

12:47.458 --> 12:48.375
Look at her.

12:48.458 --> 12:52.250
She's shaking like a Chihuahua-taur
after a cold bath. [gasps]

12:52.333 --> 12:54.166
And you didn't even notice.

12:54.250 --> 12:56.500
Do you even care about anyone?

12:57.041 --> 13:01.125
I'm sorry that I don't obsessively
mother everyone around me

13:01.208 --> 13:02.666
and control their lives.

13:02.750 --> 13:04.083
Wow.

13:04.166 --> 13:07.166
That's a Horse-pology if ever I heard one.

13:07.250 --> 13:09.125
Come on, everyone. Let's go.

13:09.208 --> 13:12.000
We've all had enough adventure
for one lifetime.

13:12.083 --> 13:13.000
[snorts]

13:14.791 --> 13:16.083
Safe travels.

13:16.708 --> 13:19.166
Hey! Have fun in your dome!

13:19.916 --> 13:21.333
[whimpering]

13:25.875 --> 13:27.208
[wind whistling]

13:28.291 --> 13:29.291
[grunts]

13:29.375 --> 13:30.375
[snorts]

13:31.583 --> 13:34.125
Eh, okay. Forget those guys anyway.

13:38.041 --> 13:39.833
Gotta get back on track. Okay.

13:39.916 --> 13:42.083
I'm a horse. I know what I'm doing.

13:42.166 --> 13:45.541
Horses, we find things.
What we're known for, right?

13:45.625 --> 13:48.208
Uh… It's, uh… Oh yeah!

13:48.291 --> 13:49.833
[dramatic music plays]

13:49.916 --> 13:51.208
[groans]

13:51.291 --> 13:52.458
Turds. [snorts]

13:53.083 --> 13:56.458
I was wrong.
Horses are not good at finding things.

13:56.541 --> 13:58.625
-Was that dogs?
-[eerie whispering]

13:58.708 --> 14:00.833
-[squealing]
-Truffle pigs? I dunno. Ah!

14:00.916 --> 14:03.833
A guy! This guy'll probably know
what's up. He has a purse.

14:03.916 --> 14:05.625
Hey-o! [chuckles nervously]

14:05.708 --> 14:09.875
Do you, uh… Do you happen to know
where I could find the Rainbow Road?

14:10.500 --> 14:13.166
[Centaur] The Rainbow Road, you say?

14:14.000 --> 14:16.750
I knew a Rainbow Road once.

14:17.375 --> 14:20.250
He stole purses from mein grandpapa.

14:20.875 --> 14:24.083
Got a lot of nerve
bringing up his name in these parts.

14:24.166 --> 14:26.833
A lot-- [coughs]

14:27.500 --> 14:28.541
A lot of nerve.

14:29.958 --> 14:31.291
Don't take mein purse.

14:33.541 --> 14:36.000
I don't want your stupid purse!

14:36.583 --> 14:37.583
Ugh!

14:37.666 --> 14:39.666
-[owl hooting]
-[sighs] It's getting dark.

14:39.750 --> 14:43.791
I don't know where I am.
I'm never getting home, am I?

14:43.875 --> 14:45.500
Hey! Murderer!

14:45.583 --> 14:47.750
-Oh boy!
-[crying]

14:47.833 --> 14:51.500
-[shushing] Oh, oh… It's okay.
-Oh, I'm sorry. I didn't--

14:51.583 --> 14:54.708
How would you like it
if I tried to smother your baby?

14:54.791 --> 14:58.583
Well, first, I'd have to imagine
a scenario where I have a baby

14:58.666 --> 15:02.916
-and then… I guess that would be not good.
-[continues crying]

15:03.000 --> 15:06.791
Just try thinking about
somebody other than yourself next time!

15:08.875 --> 15:10.375
[snorts, sighs]

15:12.041 --> 15:14.333
I am thinking about someone else.

15:15.208 --> 15:16.583
[somber music playing]

15:21.458 --> 15:23.875
♪ With you ♪

15:23.958 --> 15:26.916
And I'm probably
never gonna get to see her again.

15:27.833 --> 15:29.208
[arrow whooshes]

15:29.916 --> 15:31.375
[snarling]

15:33.083 --> 15:34.083
[sighs]

15:34.166 --> 15:35.583
[panting]

15:37.333 --> 15:39.083
[Rider echoing] No!

15:42.083 --> 15:43.291
[gasps, pants]

15:43.375 --> 15:44.750
[Rider] ♪ You're okay ♪

15:46.000 --> 15:47.375
♪ You're all right ♪

15:48.958 --> 15:52.541
♪ I'll never ever leave your side ♪

15:53.208 --> 15:55.208
[panting]

15:57.666 --> 15:58.750
♪ Don't think ♪

15:59.666 --> 16:00.750
♪ Just trust ♪

16:01.583 --> 16:04.291
♪ "Stay calm
Stay with me," she said ♪

16:05.291 --> 16:07.458
♪ Eyes open ♪

16:07.541 --> 16:11.583
♪ Breathe in
Just one wrong move, and we're dead ♪

16:13.791 --> 16:17.875
♪ And if she and I don't reunite ♪

16:18.416 --> 16:22.416
-♪ How can I go on? ♪
-[Glendale snoring] Wow.

16:22.500 --> 16:28.250
♪ Do we still remember what is gone? ♪

16:32.625 --> 16:37.750
♪ What if I forget your face? ♪

16:39.958 --> 16:44.291
♪ What if you move on without me? ♪

16:45.541 --> 16:51.875
♪ What if I can't find
The doorway back through? ♪

16:51.958 --> 16:54.500
♪ And what if I do ♪

16:55.833 --> 16:59.208
♪ But don't recognize you? ♪

17:00.333 --> 17:05.791
♪ What if I take far too long ♪

17:07.541 --> 17:12.583
♪ And the danger comes to claim you? ♪

17:13.666 --> 17:19.375
♪ What if I'm too late
To save you from your fate ♪

17:20.166 --> 17:25.666
♪ And you are lost forever 'cause of me? ♪

17:25.750 --> 17:30.250
♪ Yeah ♪

17:40.833 --> 17:43.583
♪ I will find a way ♪

17:43.666 --> 17:48.291
♪ To make sure that you're okay ♪

17:51.416 --> 17:55.875
♪ One careful step at a time ♪

17:57.083 --> 18:00.541
♪ For you and I ♪

18:02.791 --> 18:06.125
♪ Are fragile things ♪

18:08.708 --> 18:10.708
[sobbing]

18:12.625 --> 18:14.625
[squawking]

18:17.291 --> 18:18.500
[Rider] ♪ With you ♪

18:18.583 --> 18:19.833
[echoing] No!

18:19.916 --> 18:21.250
[sword swishing]

18:21.333 --> 18:22.291
[grunting]

18:22.375 --> 18:25.666
Horse, Horse, Horse, Horse.

18:25.750 --> 18:26.750
[muffled scream]

18:28.958 --> 18:31.541
[mouthful] What's going on?
What are you… Mm.

18:31.625 --> 18:33.291
[munching] Mm.

18:33.375 --> 18:35.500
What is this flavor I'm tasting?

18:35.583 --> 18:37.958
-[giggles]
-Oh, it's gigglecakes.

18:38.041 --> 18:40.375
[munching] It's really good.

18:40.458 --> 18:43.166
Not used to breakfast, clearly.

18:43.250 --> 18:44.375
[whimpering]

18:44.458 --> 18:47.375
[sighs] But… But what are you doing here?

18:47.458 --> 18:48.958
Besides force-feeding me.

18:50.083 --> 18:52.541
Nothing means more to me than my herd.

18:52.625 --> 18:55.875
And the thought
of never seeing them again terrifies me.

18:56.375 --> 18:58.958
Hmm. I'm really sorry.

18:59.583 --> 19:03.416
And nothing means more
to you than your Rider.

19:03.500 --> 19:07.083
Let our herd help you find your herd.

19:07.708 --> 19:08.916
Thank-- [grunts]

19:09.000 --> 19:11.750
But from now on, we do things my way.

19:11.833 --> 19:12.958
Understood.

19:13.041 --> 19:14.208
Uh…

19:15.083 --> 19:17.416
-Hey, look that way.
-Hmm?

19:17.500 --> 19:20.541
Aah! What-- Hold on.
I was just eating that.

19:20.625 --> 19:21.833
[burps]

19:21.916 --> 19:24.000
[scoffs] Unsanitary.

19:24.833 --> 19:28.208
Horse? Horse? Horse? Horse? Horse?

19:28.291 --> 19:31.416
-Yeah, I heard you. What do you want?
-What's a Rider?

19:31.500 --> 19:33.791
Oh, yes. Thank you. Finally.

19:33.875 --> 19:35.666
-What is a Rider anyway?
-Uh…

19:35.750 --> 19:38.333
Does a Rider like to,
you know, kid around?

19:38.416 --> 19:41.208
-Eh, in her way.
-Is a Rider a BFF?

19:41.291 --> 19:43.416
-Well…
-Or more of a BFFF?

19:43.500 --> 19:47.333
[laughs] You're not gonna know what
that stands for, so I'll tell you.

19:47.416 --> 19:49.125
A buddy for fancy frolicking.

19:49.666 --> 19:52.166
She's more of a warrior.
We fight together.

19:52.250 --> 19:55.083
-She gets on my back, and--
-She stands on you.

19:55.166 --> 19:57.375
-That's dumb.
-[laughs]

19:57.458 --> 20:01.500
Mostly, she sits. And when
she wants me to go a certain direction,

20:01.583 --> 20:02.958
she pulls on my reins.

20:03.625 --> 20:05.375
My… My reins. My--

20:05.916 --> 20:09.833
[screams] My armor! My reins!
They're all gone!

20:09.916 --> 20:13.875
[quavering] I'm completely
and utterly nude.

20:15.875 --> 20:17.583
We're all nude here.

20:17.666 --> 20:19.500
-[ominous music plays]
-[chuckles]

20:19.583 --> 20:22.500
Wait. Your Rider can make it rain?

20:22.583 --> 20:25.625
Uh-uh-uh, I thought they didn't have magic
in your world.

20:25.708 --> 20:30.875
No, not like rain from the sky. Reins.
These things that she puts over my head--

20:30.958 --> 20:32.458
[all] Oh!

20:32.541 --> 20:36.250
Yeah, no. I mean, it's more complicated
than that, but… [gasps]

20:36.333 --> 20:38.958
-Hello?
-I'm actually interested in the story.

20:39.041 --> 20:40.958
-What happens?
-You can't leave us hanging.

20:41.041 --> 20:42.041
Rider.

20:42.625 --> 20:44.625
-What is she doing?
-[Horse] Rider!

20:45.125 --> 20:47.916
-[tsks] Rude.
-Follow her!

20:48.958 --> 20:52.083
-[Zulius yelps] Ow!
-Safely! Follow her safely!

20:53.333 --> 20:54.458
[sighs]

20:55.083 --> 20:56.291
[chuckles]

21:00.958 --> 21:02.833
[closing theme music playing]

21:32.458 --> 21:34.625
[Horse galloping]

21:34.708 --> 21:36.708
[neighing]

21:37.375 --> 21:39.375
[whimsical music playing]
